n#|3|at|One commonly asked question is 

^c How can I make the text that I can see below the deal,  LARGER ?

While you cannot do this directly you can achieve the same effect by  making

^c(a)  the main aaBridge window larger  (eg: drag the lower right corner)
^c(b)  the area that the deal takes up smaller

To change the size of the deal area look in the ^*b Size & Misc ^*n option tab in the right hand column.  

Alternately (eg: on a MAC) you can go there via    ^*b  Menubar  >  Options   >   Size & Misc ^*n

there will see the  ^*bDeal Area Size^*n  setting.

Try selecting   '^*bTiny^*n'   and then moving between pages to let the new  size  settle down.



